headline: CoreWeave boost, Public Storage gain, MSCI Q1 beat
summary: US stocks (^DJI, ^GSPC, ^IXIC) gained ground, as Wall Street recovers from Monday's sell-off. CoreWeave (CRWV) shares saw a boost as analysts from Jefferies, Needham, and Stifel initiated coverage of the stock with Buy ratings. Public Storage (PSA) gained after BofA Securities upgraded its rating on the stock, and MSCI (MSCI) posted a first quarter earnings beat, but its net new recurring subscription sales fell short of expectations. Stay up to date on the latest market action, minute-by-minute, with Yahoo Finance's Market Minute.

headline: MSCI's first-quarter profit rises on robust demand for its products
summary: Market volatility driven by economic uncertainty following U.S. President Donald Trump's tariff announcements has prompted asset managers to swiftly adjust their portfolios, leading to greater demand for data and analytics services provided by companies such as MSCI.  Recurring subscriptions in its index segment rose 9.6% to $233.3 million in the first quarter from a year earlier, driven by growth from market-cap weighted index products.

headline: MSCI Reports Financial Results for First Quarter 2025
summary: NEW YORK, April 22, 2025--MSCI Inc. ("MSCI" or the "Company") (NYSE: MSCI), a leading provider of critical decision support tools and services for the global investment community, today announced its financial results for the three months ended March 31, 2025 ("first quarter 2025").
